description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to recruit a Team Leader to join the operational management team for Public Health Immunisation Team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The candidate should be a motivated, enthusiastic and dynamic Specialist Community Public Health Nurse – (NMC part 3) with excellent knowledge, skills, experience and proven leadership qualities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will need to provide clinical leadership, direction and encourage development of the teams in order to improve quality and shape services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will support teams to ensure effective implementation of the pre-school, BCG clinics and schools immunisation programme.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for leadership and professional development within a dynamic and forward thinking service. Consideration will be given to candidates with relevant knowledge and skills on a part time basis and/or dual roles within Public Health Nursing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Angela Phillips - Senior Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;angela.phillips@wales.nhs.co.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01443 802774&lt;/p&gt;
